cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM

The paper deals with computer vision and image processing, specifically novel view extrapolation. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions depth estimation and refinement, which are common topics in computer graphics (cs.GR). The use of image priors and the combination of learned models and depth uncertainty suggest that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions magnification, which suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
